=== AEB CAN Module — Fault Injection (ISO 26262-6 Tab.11) ===

--- Category A: Invalid values (NULL pointers, bad DLC, unknown ID, HAL fault) ---
  PASS  A1  brake_cmd(NULL,pid,fsm) -> CAN_ERR_TX
  PASS  A2  brake_cmd(state,NULL,fsm) -> CAN_ERR_TX
  PASS  A3  brake_cmd(state,pid,NULL) -> CAN_ERR_TX
  PASS  A4  fsm_state(NULL,fsm) -> CAN_ERR_TX
  PASS  A5  fsm_state(state,NULL) -> CAN_ERR_TX
  PASS  A6  alert(NULL) -> CAN_ERR_TX
  PASS  A7  rx_process(NULL,id,data,dlc) -> no crash
  PASS  A8  rx_process(state,id,NULL,dlc) -> no crash
  PASS  A9  check_timeout(NULL) -> no crash
  PASS  A10 get_rx_data(NULL,dst) -> no crash
  PASS  A11 get_rx_data(state,NULL) -> no crash
  PASS  A12 rx(EgoVehicle, dlc=4<8) -> no decode
  PASS  A13 rx(RadarTarget, dlc=0) -> no decode
  PASS  A14 rx(unknown ID) -> no TX side-effect
  PASS  A15 init with forced HAL failure -> CAN_ERR_INIT, initialised=0

--- Category B: Numeric extremes (NaN, Inf, encode overflow, pack overflow) ---
  PASS  B1  brake_bar=NaN -> returns, does not abort
  PASS  B2  brake_bar=+Inf -> returns, does not abort
  PASS  B3  brake_bar=-Inf -> returns, does not abort
  PASS  B3b packed BrakePressure after -Inf == 0 (clamped)
  PASS  B4  brake_bar=1e5 -> adjacent signals intact
  PASS  B5  brake_bar=FLT_MAX -> does not abort
  PASS  B6  pack(0xFFFFFFFF, len=4) -> masked, no bleed

--- Category C: State corruption (SEU on alive_counter, rx_miss, cycle_counter) ---
  PASS  C1  alive_counter=0xAA -> bounded after next TX
  PASS  C2  rx_miss_count=0xFF -> saturates at 0xFF (no wrap)
  PASS  C2b rx_miss_count=0xFF -> timeout_flag=1
  PASS  C3  tx_cycle_counter=UINT32_MAX -> wraps safely, no TX
  PASS  C4  initialised=0x55 -> no observable effect (informational)

--- Category D: Persistence (timeout recovery, 100 toggles, TX burst) ---
  PASS  D1a 10 ticks no RX -> timeout_flag=1
  PASS  D1b valid radar frame -> miss_count=0, flag cleared
  PASS  D2  100 send_fail toggles -> rc matches toggle state
  PASS  D3  TX burst > buffer -> CAN_ERR_TX surfaces (expected ~32)

